'''Mary Franklin''' is the former Sr. Events Lead for [[Lucasfilm]], a position in which she coordinated various marketing and promotional events for the company, including [[Celebration|''Star Wars'' Celebration]], the yearly E3 Expo, Licensing Show, and San Diego Comic-Con International. Franklin worked for Lucasfilm from [[2001]] to [[2015]], when she joined [[Wikipedia:Reed Exhibitions|ReedPOP]], a company that runs pop culture conventions worldwide and a Lucasfilm licensee with whom Franklin has worked with on ''Star Wars'' Celebration, as its global event director.

Franklin is the former editor of ''[[Bantha Tracks (newsletter)|Bantha Tracks]]'', a ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine department focusing on ''[[Star Wars]]'' fans. Her run ended with [[Star Wars Insider 157|issue 157]], after which editorial duties passed to author [[Pete Vilmur]].

